Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a grey-brown pottery vessel, the interior is lightly covered with a dark-brown resinous deposit, the exterior is covered with a cream-coloured slip and faint traces of at least five lines of black-painted demotic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393808) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393808)
